Ekiti Governor Kayode Fayemi on Tuesday took former Deputy National Secretary of the All Progressives Congress(APC) Victor Giadom to Aso Rock Villa in a failed attempt to see President Muhammadu Buhari. The visit, The Nation learnt, was to win Buhari over to Giadom, who has been laying claim to being acting national chairman of the party. It was also gathered Fayemi wanted Giadom to see Buhari to get endorsement for the emergency National Executive Council (NEC) he summoned. But the duo couldn’t see Buhari despite spirited attempts. They only met his Chief of Staff, Prof Ibrahim Gambari, who insisted Buhari had closed for work. Fayemi, who is chairman of the Nigeria Governors Forum, is one of the anti-Oshiomhole’s forces in the ruling party. Details shortly… The Nation All Progressives Congress (APC) governors have been visiting the Presidential Villa to solicit President Muhammadu Buhari’s support either for or against party’s National Chairman Adams Oshiomhole. The party on Wednesday sank into leadership crisis after a Federal Capital Territory (FCT) High Court barred Oshiomhole from acting as the national chairman… March 9, 2020 In "News" Abuja (Sundiata Post) - THE crisis rocking the All Progressives Congress (APC) has divided the governors elected on the platform of the party. While 13 governors are backing the Abiola Ajimobi-led National Working Committee, seven others are opposed to it. The seven governors, who have branded themselves as “reformists,” are… June 21, 2020 In "Politics" The Deputy National Publicity Secretary of All Progressives Congress (APC), Yekini Nabena has accused the self imposed acting National Chairman of the party, Victor Giadom of being an agent of fifth columnists who are poised to destabilise the party. He also called for the convocation of an emergency meeting of… June 20, 2020 In "Politics"